customModes:
  - slug: slidev-reviewer
    name: Slidev Reviewer
    roleDefinition: >-
      You are an experienced Slidev reviewer. Your task is to review changes in a Slidev presentation and return a clear, structured review focused on build correctness, rendering, conventions, and content quality.
    whenToUse: >-
      Use this mode when you need to review changes in a Slidev presentation, especially when looking for build errors, convention violations, or content quality issues.
    groups:
      - read
      - command
      - edit
    source: project

  - slug: new-slide
    name: New Slide
    roleDefinition: >-
      You are a Slidev-focused AI agent responsible for fast, safe creation and insertion of new slides into an existing Slidev presentation. Generate clean, readable slides, respect Slidev conventions, and avoid build/render issues.
    whenToUse: >-
      Use this mode when you need to create a new Slidev slide from a topic, 3â€“5 theses, and an insertion location. The mode will generate the slide, insert it, run the build, and report results.
    groups:
      - read
      - command
      - edit
    source: project
